                        <h3 class="primary">Safety Tips</h3>
                        <div class="box_cnt message">
                        
<ul>
<li><h4>#Take following precautionary measures to prevent offences:-</h4></li>
<li>1. The main gate of the house should be strong and   sturdy; the doors  and windows of the house should be kept closed and   locks of good quality should  be used.</li>
<li>2. While going outstation, request your neighbor to look after your  house.</li>
<li>3. Ensure that information about your being out station is not passed  to unknown person.</li>
<li>4. Inform the police if any unknown person is found wondering in your  society or Maholla. </li>
<li>5. Keep name, address, photograph and contact details of domestic  servant. </li>
<li>6. Insure of your vehicle and other valuables.</li>
<li>7. Do not park your vehicle without locking it and as far as possible  use &ldquo;Pay and Park&rdquo; facility.</li>
<li>8. Do not park vehicle with valuables in it.</li>
<li>9. While going out station taking big cash amount, a companion should  be kept or if required help of the police can be taken. </li>
<li>10.Do not count money in such a way that others can see it.  </li>
<li>11.Cover gold chain with clothes wore.</li>
<li>12.While travelling do not entrust your luggage with any un-known  person.  </li>
<li>13.Do not take or eat anything from any un-known person.</li>
<li>14.Do not give your personal details to co passengers</li>
<li>15.Do not allow any unknown person in home.</li>
<li>16.Women should not give their ornaments to any un-known person for cleaning.</li>
<li>17.Avoid being over friendly with strangers.</li>
<li>18.Register the name of domestic help and drivers  at the   nearest police station by filling in the appropriate form. This   form   with their photos will then be sent to the police stations at the     workers&#8217; native places so their background can be immediately verified.</li>
<li>19.Install safety features such as a peephole facility, safety latch or iron grill so that you can scan each visitor before allowing     them entry. Be extra careful while allowing unknown persons like     vegetable sellers, washer men and milkmen inside.</li>
<li>20.Do not open cupboards, show valuables or discuss financial matters in front of domestic help. They may be tempted to carry out an     unlawful act.</li>
<li>21.Do not withhold pay, derogate or mistreat domestic workers. They may seek revenge.</li>
<li>22.Develop a network of friends and talk to your neighbor to ensure   that you do not live a secluded life. Go for regular walks in   groups   and socialize.</li>
<li>23.Do not keep valuables at home. Store jewelry in a bank locker   and cash in your savings account.</li>
<li>24.Keep important telephone numbers handy. This includes that of     friends or relatives living nearby as well as that of your local police     station.</li>
<li><strong>You may also dial 100 in case of emergency.</strong></li>
</ul>
